A 57-year-old pedestrian is in a critical condition after he was struck by a minibus in Fife.
Police said the man was injured by a silver Mercedes Vito while crossing the road at Chapel Level roundabout in Kirkcaldy.
Officers said the incident happened at about 11:05 on Friday and urged anyone with information to get in touch.
The man is being treated at the Royal Infirmary of Edinburgh. The occupants of the minibus were not injured. 
Sgt Lee Walkingshaw said: "Chapel Level Roundabout is a busy junction so I am appealing to people who were in the area and witnessed the incident to come forward. 
"I am particularly keen to hear from motorists with dashcams as they may have captured footage that will assist our investigation."
